      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening justified for titanium alloy screw under monotonic quasi-static loading.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V screw modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening. Rate-dependent effects negligible at quasi-static test speed (2 mm/min). Polyethylene block modeled as linear elastic within small-displacement regime relevant to stiffness QoI. Model form consistent with established literature for F1717 FEA."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of same material lot; geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of test articles.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (E = 114 ± 3 GPa) and yield strength (σ_y = 880 ± 15 MPa) obtained from tensile coupon tests on same Ti-6Al-4V lot as test constructs. Screw geometry from CMM measurements (n=5 screws). Input distributions characterised and propagated via Monte Carlo (500 samples) to quantify prediction uncertainty. Dominant input drivers will be characterised in a planned follow-on sensitivity analysis study; the present UQ sweep covers the full joint input space."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
