      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to clinical failure modes (fracture, excessive deformation) and are measurable in both simulation and experiment.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs mandated by ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to clinical failure by fatigue crack initiation and permanent deformation. All three are extractable from both FEA load-displacement curves and experimental test machine output."
    },
