  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required level. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 1 against a required level 2 due to single-configuration testing; this gap is accepted given that the ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration is the primary regulatory submission load case and the E/uval metric is satisfied with margin across all QoIs. Uncertainty quantification via Monte Carlo propagation of input distributions has been completed and confirms prediction intervals bracket experimental observations. The assessment team notes that a formal sensitivity analysis to rank input drivers has not yet been conducted and is planned for a follow-on study; the current UQ results are considered sufficient for the medium assurance level determination at this stage.",
